{"experienceId":"draft-6f77e1f1-14e1-4441-9c1f-123c0460dc28","title":"外汇崩盘案例-委内瑞拉","contentVersion":"draft.acd6a12c49b0","mediaFingerprint":"sha256:acd6a12c49b0cf42af2537f515b9e66350fea3c5fa6726fccda426302637ee46","publishStatus":"draft","blockers":["HUMAN_REVIEW_REQUIRED"],"evidence":[{"evidenceId":"asr-73489d9140f9a89f","startMs":40,"endMs":2920,"text":"我们来看两个陷入危机导致外汇崩盘的国家。"},{"evidenceId":"asr-69a3956290f72d2b","startMs":4200,"endMs":7000,"text":"委内瑞拉，这可是全球石油储备最多的国家。"},{"evidenceId":"asr-7ce26ac5357d07d6","startMs":7040,"endMs":12040,"text":"可是呢，因为内部各种的政治原因，美国还对它制裁，持续20年严重的经济危机。"},{"evidenceId":"asr-95927b4a94719062","startMs":12160,"endMs":16040,"text":"就我感觉哈，危机这个词已经不足以形容委内瑞拉了，可能都太轻了。"},{"evidenceId":"asr-06d4a2f92cbd21a8","startMs":16080,"endMs":23800,"text":"据2021年的统计，委内瑞拉有94.5%的人生活在贫困线以下，有76.6%的人处于极度贫困，谋杀率世界第一。"},{"evidenceId":"asr-c4828daa0420ef5a","startMs":24910,"endMs":29310,"text":"你就看这么个政治动荡、经济危机的国家，你说它货币怎么可能好？"},{"evidenceId":"asr-b4734dac5bad3266","startMs":29310,"endMs":29550,"text":"对吧？"},{"evidenceId":"asr-4bd24531480880e1","startMs":29590,"endMs":41870,"text":"2010年的官方汇率是1美元兑2.15玻利瓦尔，2014年在黑市上是1美元兑100玻利瓦尔，2016年是3000， 2018年2月是2.5万，而到半年后，1美元就只能兑25万玻利瓦尔了。"},{"evidenceId":"asr-d56fd278241d3416","startMs":42050,"endMs":43010,"text":"而这都还是小波动。"},{"evidenceId":"asr-936673d5e9964897","startMs":43250,"endMs":46490,"text":"之后，委内瑞拉又经历了恶性的通货膨胀，这汇率就更止不住了。"},{"evidenceId":"asr-33c19e60c4889a1b","startMs":46490,"endMs":54890,"text":"你看看这个是它对美元的汇率哈，注意这里边的纵轴，它是对数坐标，它是指数级往上蹿的，最后一美元已经能兑一万亿玻利瓦尔了。"},{"evidenceId":"asr-509aaf17107f031d","startMs":55470,"endMs":56670,"text":"我再给大家举个例子哈。"},{"evidenceId":"asr-02e28a1cd08d193b","startMs":56910,"endMs":60270,"text":"哎，我先考考你，你知道非洲最大的三个经济体是谁吗？"},{"evidenceId":"asr-4e97a76cda6c442d","startMs":60270,"endMs":62750,"text":"就是埃及、尼日利亚和南非。"},{"evidenceId":"asr-9aaf5df575e9e11d","startMs":63030,"endMs":64310,"text":"哎，我就想说这个尼日利亚。"},{"evidenceId":"asr-103b1f185ab28ad7","startMs":65610,"endMs":68010,"text":"他可是2亿多人口的大国，也闹幺蛾子。"},{"evidenceId":"asr-5229a639718dd4f9","startMs":68050,"endMs":71330,"text":"2022年的时候宣布说要重新设计他的大面额纸币。"},{"evidenceId":"asr-a37738c4ae255f91","startMs":71450,"endMs":74890,"text":"哎，两个月以后哈，原来旧的那些钱就全作废了，你们赶紧去银行换新的。"},{"evidenceId":"asr-c125a09ec151dbfd","startMs":74890,"endMs":76170,"text":"大家一下就慌了呀，对吧？"},{"evidenceId":"asr-798e372c538b4437","startMs":76210,"endMs":78490,"text":"干什么活啊，赶紧去银行排队等着换钱吧！"},{"evidenceId":"asr-5c8372de6d1f45a7","startMs":78920,"endMs":83760,"text":"哎，看过咱们之前聊印度经济的朋友哈，可能还记得印度它在2016年的时候就也干过类似的事。"},{"evidenceId":"asr-633ae8c438b14cc0","startMs":83840,"endMs":86920,"text":"这么做的原因呢，主要是为了遏制黑市啊，反腐败啊等等。"},{"evidenceId":"asr-ced3a90884030aac","startMs":86960,"endMs":93480,"text":"但是它短期内对经济的打击实在是太大了，尤其是你看尼日利亚又在一个全球性通货膨胀、能源危机的时候，整这么一出。"},{"evidenceId":"asr-96d5e94f0d7025fc","startMs":93560,"endMs":97000,"text":"他还取消了燃油补贴，就导致尼日利亚奈拉持续崩盘。"},{"evidenceId":"asr-26585f0220cc2718","startMs":97120,"endMs":100480,"text":"这反过来又加速了他们国内的通货膨胀，现在已经超过了30%。"},{"evidenceId":"asr-52ce0c3971860ef0","startMs":100560,"endMs":102360,"text":"国内也开始出现大规模的罢工。"},{"evidenceId":"asr-63eb86f89d03a335","startMs":102600,"endMs":105560,"text":"你看啊，这个也是一个陷入危机导致货币下跌的例子。"},{"evidenceId":"asr-d90c11bc85233e81","startMs":105600,"endMs":109800,"text":"其实最近类似的像阿根廷、埃及、斯里兰卡等等，类似的例子其实非常多。"}],"concepts":[{"conceptId":"c-venezuela-political-instability","name":"Venezuela political instability and internal political causes","firstMentionMs":7040,"isCore":true,"evidenceIds":["asr-7ce26ac5357d07d6","asr-c4828daa0420ef5a"]},{"conceptId":"c-us-sanctions-venezuela","name":"US sanctions on Venezuela","firstMentionMs":7040,"isCore":true,"evidenceIds":["asr-7ce26ac5357d07d6"]},{"conceptId":"c-venezuela-economic-crisis","name":"Venezuela's prolonged economic crisis","firstMentionMs":7040,"isCore":true,"evidenceIds":["asr-7ce26ac5357d07d6","asr-95927b4a94719062","asr-c4828daa0420ef5a"]},{"conceptId":"c-venezuela-hyperinflation","name":"Venezuelan hyperinflation","firstMentionMs":43250,"isCore":true,"evidenceIds":["asr-936673d5e9964897","asr-33c19e60c4889a1b"]},{"conceptId":"c-bolivar-depreciation","name":"Bolívar depreciation against the US dollar","firstMentionMs":29590,"isCore":true,"evidenceIds":["asr-4bd24531480880e1","asr-33c19e60c4889a1b"]},{"conceptId":"c-venezuela-poverty","name":"Venezuelan poverty and social distress","firstMentionMs":16080,"isCore":false,"evidenceIds":["asr-06d4a2f92cbd21a8"]},{"conceptId":"c-nigeria-currency-redesign","name":"Nigeria's 2022 large-denomination currency redesign","firstMentionMs":68050,"isCore":true,"evidenceIds":["asr-5229a639718dd4f9","asr-a37738c4ae255f91","asr-c125a09ec151dbfd"]},{"conceptId":"c-nigeria-fuel-subsidy-removal","name":"Nigeria's removal of fuel subsidies","firstMentionMs":93560,"isCore":true,"evidenceIds":["asr-96d5e94f0d7025fc"]},{"conceptId":"c-nigeria-inflation","name":"Nigerian inflation above 30%","firstMentionMs":97120,"isCore":true,"evidenceIds":["asr-26585f0220cc2718"]},{"conceptId":"c-naira-depreciation","name":"Naira collapse against major currencies","firstMentionMs":93560,"isCore":true,"evidenceIds":["asr-96d5e94f0d7025fc"]},{"conceptId":"c-global-inflation-energy-crisis","name":"Global inflation and energy crisis backdrop","firstMentionMs":86960,"isCore":false,"evidenceIds":["asr-ced3a90884030aac"]},{"conceptId":"c-african-largest-economies","name":"Africa's three largest economies (Egypt, Nigeria, South Africa)","firstMentionMs":56910,"isCore":false,"evidenceIds":["asr-02e28a1cd08d193b","asr-4e97a76cda6c442d"]}],"claims":[{"claimId":"cl-venezuela-20-year-crisis","statement":"Venezuela has endured roughly twenty years of severe economic crisis driven by internal politics and US sanctions.","assetClass":"fx","assertedDirection":"pressure_dominant","evidenceIds":["asr-7ce26ac5357d07d6","asr-c4828daa0420ef5a"]},{"claimId":"cl-bolivar-rate-history","statement":"Bolívar/USD moved from an official 2.15 (2010) to black-market 100 (2014), 3,000 (2016), 25,000 (Feb 2018), and 250,000 within months — and ultimately to a trillion bolívars per dollar under hyperinflation.","assetClass":"fx","assertedDirection":"pressure_dominant","evidenceIds":["asr-4bd24531480880e1","asr-33c19e60c4889a1b"]},{"claimId":"cl-nigeria-currency-redesign-2022","statement":"In 2022 Nigeria announced a redesign of its large-denomination banknotes, invalidating older notes after roughly two months.","assetClass":"fx","assertedDirection":"pressure_dominant","evidenceIds":["asr-5229a639718dd4f9","asr-a37738c4ae255f91","asr-c125a09ec151dbfd","asr-798e372c538b4437"]},{"claimId":"cl-nigeria-fuel-subsidy-removed","statement":"Nigeria removed fuel subsidies, contributing to a sustained naira collapse.","assetClass":"fx","assertedDirection":"pressure_dominant","evidenceIds":["asr-96d5e94f0d7025fc"]},{"claimId":"cl-nigeria-inflation-30pct","statement":"Nigeria's domestic inflation has exceeded 30%, accelerating from the naira's decline.","assetClass":"fx","assertedDirection":"pressure_dominant","evidenceIds":["asr-26585f0220cc2718"]},{"claimId":"cl-currency-crisis-pattern","statement":"Currency collapses driven by domestic crises are a recurring pattern across countries such as Venezuela, Nigeria, Argentina, Egypt and Sri Lanka.","assetClass":"fx","assertedDirection":"support_dominant","evidenceIds":["asr-63eb86f89d03a335","asr-d90c11bc85233e81","asr-73489d9140f9a89f"]}],"causalEdges":[{"edgeId":"e-political-snap-crisis","from":{"nodeType":"concept","nodeId":"c-venezuela-political-instability"},"to":{"nodeType":"concept","nodeId":"c-venezuela-economic-crisis"},"mechanism":"Political turmoil disrupts fiscal and monetary stability, eroding productive capacity.","omittedIntermediate":false,"evidenceIds":["asr-7ce26ac5357d07d6","asr-c4828daa0420ef5a"]},{"edgeId":"e-sanctions-crisis","from":{"nodeType":"concept","nodeId":"c-us-sanctions-venezuela"},"to":{"nodeType":"concept","nodeId":"c-venezuela-economic-crisis"},"mechanism":"External sanctions restrict trade, financing and revenue channels, deepening the domestic downturn.","omittedIntermediate":false,"evidenceIds":["asr-7ce26ac5357d07d6"]},{"edgeId":"e-crisis-bolivar","from":{"nodeType":"concept","nodeId":"c-venezuela-economic-crisis"},"to":{"nodeType":"concept","nodeId":"c-bolivar-depreciation"},"mechanism":"Political and economic instability destroys confidence in the local currency, driving capital flight and pushing the exchange rate higher.","omittedIntermediate":false,"evidenceIds":["asr-c4828daa0420ef5a","asr-b4734dac5bad3266","asr-4bd24531480880e1"]},{"edgeId":"e-hyperinflation-bolivar","from":{"nodeType":"concept","nodeId":"c-venezuela-hyperinflation"},"to":{"nodeType":"concept","nodeId":"c-bolivar-depreciation"},"mechanism":"Rampant domestic price inflation erodes purchasing power of the currency, accelerating its depreciation on a logarithmic trajectory.","omittedIntermediate":false,"evidenceIds":["asr-936673d5e9964897","asr-33c19e60c4889a1b","asr-d56fd278241d3416"]},{"edgeId":"e-redesign-panic","from":{"nodeType":"concept","nodeId":"c-nigeria-currency-redesign"},"to":{"nodeType":"claim","nodeId":"cl-nigeria-currency-redesign-2022"},"mechanism":"Sudden invalidation of old notes triggers panic, bank queues and economic disruption in the short term.","omittedIntermediate":false,"evidenceIds":["asr-a37738c4ae255f91","asr-c125a09ec151dbfd","asr-798e372c538b4437"]},{"edgeId":"e-subsidy-naira","from":{"nodeType":"concept","nodeId":"c-nigeria-fuel-subsidy-removal"},"to":{"nodeType":"concept","nodeId":"c-naira-depreciation"},"mechanism":"Removing fuel subsidies raises imported energy costs, worsens the trade balance, and pressures the currency.","omittedIntermediate":false,"evidenceIds":["asr-96d5e94f0d7025fc"]},{"edgeId":"e-naira-inflation","from":{"nodeType":"concept","nodeId":"c-naira-depreciation"},"to":{"nodeType":"concept","nodeId":"c-nigeria-inflation"},"mechanism":"A weaker naira makes imports more expensive, which feeds back into domestic consumer prices above 30%.","omittedIntermediate":false,"evidenceIds":["asr-26585f0220cc2718"]},{"edgeId":"e-inflation-strikes","from":{"nodeType":"concept","nodeId":"c-nigeria-inflation"},"to":{"nodeType":"claim","nodeId":"cl-nigeria-strikes"},"mechanism":"Rising prices and a falling currency reduce real wages, prompting large-scale labor strikes.","omittedIntermediate":true,"evidenceIds":["asr-52ce0c3971860ef0","asr-26585f0220cc2718"]},{"edgeId":"e-crisis-pattern","from":{"nodeType":"claim","nodeId":"cl-bolivar-rate-history"},"to":{"nodeType":"claim","nodeId":"cl-currency-crisis-pattern"},"mechanism":"Repeated empirical examples (Venezuela, Nigeria, Argentina, Egypt, Sri Lanka) generalize into a recurring pattern of crisis-driven currency collapse.","omittedIntermediate":true,"evidenceIds":["asr-63eb86f89d03a335","asr-d90c11bc85233e81"]}],"conditions":[{"conditionId":"cond-global-inflation-context","variable":"global_inflation_environment","operator":"above","affectsEdgeId":"e-redesign-naira","statement":"If a global inflation and energy crisis is in effect, Nigeria's policy shocks produce a markedly larger naira decline.","evidenceIds":["asr-ced3a90884030aac"]}],"triggerCandidates":[],"rejectedTriggerCandidates":[{"candidateId":"cue-ev-subsidy-naira-collapse","reason":"MIN_GAP_VIOLATION"},{"candidateId":"cue-ev-nigeria-currency-redesign","reason":"MIN_GAP_VIOLATION"},{"candidateId":"cue-ev-global-context-condition","reason":"MIN_GAP_VIOLATION"},{"candidateId":"cue-ev-other-countries-pattern","reason":"MIN_GAP_VIOLATION"},{"candidateId":"cue-ev-strikes-social-impact","reason":"MIN_GAP_VIOLATION"},{"candidateId":"cue-ev-venezuela-poverty-data","reason":"MIN_GAP_VIOLATION"},{"candidateId":"cue-ev-quiz-transition","reason":"MIN_GAP_VIOLATION"},{"candidateId":"c-currency-crisis-pattern","reason":"REPAIR_EXHAUSTED"},{"candidateId":"cl-venezuela-largest-oil-reserves","reason":"REPAIR_EXHAUSTED"},{"candidateId":"cl-venezuela-poverty-2021","reason":"REPAIR_EXHAUSTED"},{"candidateId":"cl-venezuela-murder-rate","reason":"REPAIR_EXHAUSTED"},{"candi